						               													<description>Devil's Chess is a deck of cards that compliments traditional chess.  It is easy to learn, infinitely re-playable, and is wildly addictive.  Devil's Chess brings modern board game mechanics to an old classic.  With Devil's Chess you get a bit of randomness, new mechanics and card combos, and a whole lot of new tricks to surprise your opponent. Devil's Chess brings Chess out of the 6th century and into the 21st!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setting up the game is easy.  Shuffle both decks, and set them to the left and right of the chessboard.  Each player is dealt a hand of three Playable Cards. To begin the game flip over one Rule Card.  Players then take turns playing cards and moving pieces.  When a player draws a &amp;ldquo;Devil&amp;rsquo;s Chess&amp;rdquo; card, another new Rule Card is flipped over.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     At the beginning of your turn, draw a Playable card if you do not have three&amp;#10;     You may use or discard one Playable Card&amp;#10;     Your turn ends after you move a chess piece&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is over when a King is put into checkmate or when a &amp;ldquo;More Ways to Win!&amp;rdquo; condition is met by a player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With 30 unique Rule Cards and 90 Playable Cards, Devil&amp;rsquo;s Chess is unbelievably re-playable.  We know you&amp;rsquo;ll make it a mainstay in your game library.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
